[1] Serotype 3
Date: Fri 15 Jan 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(03) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=19512


Bluetongue, Brazil
------------------
Information received on [and dated] 15 Jan 2016 from Dr Guilherme Henrique Figueiredo Marques, director, [Animal Health Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Food Supply of Brazil], Brasilia, Brazil

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 11 Mar 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 22 Dec 2015
Date event resolved: 26 Jun 2015
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: bluetongue virus
Serotype: 3
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1(410830400131): Foz do Iguacu, Parana
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Mar 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 26 Jun 2015
Epidemiological unit: zoo
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Pygmy brocket: _Mazama nana_ (Cervidae) / 30 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the native animals (_Mazama nana_, pygmy brocket) were in a zoo in an ecological reserve owned by the company Itaipu Binacional, at Foz do Iguacu, Parana, Brazil.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Pygmy brocket: _Mazama nana_ (Cervidae) / 3 / 3 / 100 / 3
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments
From March to June 2015, 4 deer (_Mazama nana_) in a zoo in an ecological reserve of the company Itaipu Binacional showed clinical signs and death. As part of a research project on diseases in cervids in the ecological reserve, samples were sent to the Research Laboratory on Animal Virology of the Federal University of Minas Gerais and tested negative for epizootic haemorrhagic disease virus and positive for bluetongue virus. The samples were tested by viral isolation and typing and serotype 3 of bluetongue virus was identified in one animal.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of vectors; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Research Laboratory on Animal Virology of the Federal University of Minas Gerais (local laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Pygmy brocket / real-time reverse transcriptase / polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 22 Dec 2015 / Positive
Pygmy brocket / serotyping / 22 Dec 2015 / Positive
Pygmy brocket / virus isolation / 22 Dec 2015 / Positive
Pygmy brocket / virus sequencing / 22 Dec 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

